<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="319" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,153,287]" pageId="3" pageNumber="319">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,225,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="319">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[828,912,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="319">batillus</emphasis>
(= shovel) with a Latin superlative ending 
<emphasis box="[1381,1430,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="319">-osa</emphasis>
, referring to the shovel-shaped labial palpus.
</paragraph>
